--- !u!114 &1139109525
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1139109524}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: d806c0ed1dff07d458f348b3e123f9c8, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::NarrativeManagerScript
  events:
  - eventName: Player Spawn Event
    dialogues:
    - Hello! Whenever you feel ready, please proceed to the first test room.
    narratorClip: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 59d47bbff549d9c488b601efd40ededc, type: 3}
    delayBefore: 2
    delayAfter: 0.1
  - eventName: First variant of ColorPatternTest
    dialogues:
    - 'In this first test, you will be shown a random sequence of buttons light up
      one by one, and you will then need to memorize it and recreate it after its
      finished. '
    narratorClip: {fileID: 8300000, guid: bd34321fba6a0e842a2b424f1cad1e01, type: 3}
    delayBefore: 1
    delayAfter: 1
  - eventName: Second variant of ColorPatternTest
    dialogues:
    - Now, we will test reverse pattern recognition. Basically, you will need to
      introduce the sequence given but in reversed order. Get ready.
    narratorClip: {fileID: 0}
    delayBefore: 1
    delayAfter: 1
  - eventName: Minigame Success
    dialogues:
    - You got it right! Well done.
    narratorClip: {fileID: 0}
    delayBefore: 0.1
    delayAfter: 0.1
  - eventName: Minigame Failure
    dialogues:
    - Not quite the right sequence, but don't worry, we are not measuring results,
      only the way you answer.
    narratorClip: {fileID: 0}
    delayBefore: 0.1
    delayAfter: 0.1
  - eventName: End of ColorPatternTest
    dialogues:
    - First evaluation complete. Your responses were... within expected parameters.
      Please proceed to room two at your own pace. There is no rush.
    narratorClip: {fileID: 0}
    delayBefore: 0.1
    delayAfter: 0.1
  - eventName: ImageAssociationTest
    dialogues:
    - In this second test, you will be shown different scenarios and you will then
      need to pick the word that better first the image from the options below the
      screen.
    narratorClip: {fileID: 0}
    delayBefore: 0.1
    delayAfter: 0.1
  narratorTextScript: {fileID: 1380830024}
  colorPatternTestScript: {fileID: 8854637723345381251}
